    "narrative": "For this April 7th slate, the Zurich Zebras lean heavily on high-ceiling power-speed combinations, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** and **Junior Caminero**. **Yordan Alvarez** posts our highest efficiency score of the day (79.83) thanks to a massive +14% park factor and a favorable matchup against Freeland, while **Junior Caminero** (75.43) capitalizes on a high-leverage spot in the order against a beatable arm in Assad. Meanwhile, **Trea Turner** (70.50) remains a must-start; despite a respectable opposing arm in Ray, the combination of a wind-out environment and the leadoff slot provides the necessary cushion to keep his daily efficiency well into the \"Strong\" territory.\n\nOur most critical lineup construction success today is the usage of **Colt Keith** (68.93) and **Kyle Schwarber** (68.71). **Colt Keith** thrives in the leadoff spot against Bradley, benefiting from a +10% order boost that elevates him well above our marginal threshold. Similarly, **Kyle Schwarber** continues to profile as an elite asset; despite facing Ray, his 0.402 xwOBA and the wind-aided park boost secure his spot. We keep a close eye on **Victor Scott II** (52.99), whose elite sprint speed is a staple for our stolen base-starved roster; while his score is modest, his ability to manufacture runs at the bottom of the lineup keeps him in the starting nine over lower-upside depth pieces.\n\nThe most difficult personnel decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion**, who fell just shy of our start threshold with a 39.80 score. While the platoon advantage against S\u00e1nchez was enticing, the combination of a tough opposing arm and a lower position in the batting order pushed him into the \"Below Floor\" category, forcing us to bench him to preserve our limited game caps. We remain wary of the risk surrounding **Kazuma Okamoto** (44.09), who faces a formidable test against Yamamoto; his score is dragged down by a -16% skill penalty against the pitcher, and he remains our most volatile start. As we monitor today\u2019s action, players like **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Logan O'Hoppe**, **Caleb Durbin**, **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, and **Luis Pena** are held in reserve, ready to address any late-breaking lineup changes or inclement weather developments.",
